FBIS4-4551 "dreas064__a94002" FBIS-EAS-94-064-A Daily Report 4 April 1994 ANNEX Japan Reaction to U.S. Report on Trade Barriers Reaction to U.S. Report on Trade Barriers Hosokawa Responds OW0204024894 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 2 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW0204024894 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database Japanese BFN [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 1 April Evening Edition] [Text] The U.S. trade representative has released an annual report on foreign trade barriers that cites the procurement of the Japanese Government. Asked by a group of reporters in the Diet building to comment on the annunal report, Prime Minister Hosokawa said: "The annual report urges the Japanese Government to map out another package of measures to open up the Japanese market by June. From now on, the government will take voluntary measures to open up the Japanese market." In this way, the prime minister stressed that the Japanese Government plans to do everything in its power to map out another package of measures during June to open markets in Japan.
